<br>
Sorry to trouble people, but I've reached the stage in my epic quest of, you guessed it, the final battle. And I'm going to need a bit of a hand, so any help would rock! I'm looking for about 2 to 3 groups... at least 2 beefy tanks and 2 clerics, plus all the others that make a raid successful and fun.<br>
<br>
Details...<br>
DAY: Thursday, June 19<br>
TIME: 7pm PST (please start gathering around 6:30-45 if possible)<br>
PLACE: Lake of Ill Omen, on the East side of the lake near the water's edge, right by the goblin ruins. The FV stone from poK should be your fastest route to the Lake.<br>
CHANNEL: fist<br>
<br>
For those curious about the event, I have an item called Eye of Kaiaren. I turn this in to an astral projection on a platform in the lake. This spawns 2 mobs... Deep and Vorash (hence the 2 tanks =). I'll pull both these to the raid. Once these are defeated, a creature called Xenovorash spawns on the platform. I'll again pull this lone mob to the raid on shore. We kill this thing, and ta-da!! One Demon Fang for turn in coming up!!<br>
<br>
Whole event is triggered from an item I already have and Xenovorash spawns instantly upon the death of Vorash, so there's no waiting for spawn times, etc. Because of this, the raid shouldn't take up more than an hour of your time... including buffing, grouping, etc.<br>
<br>
Finally, any costs incurred from the event... like from peridots... will be covered by me.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, thank you very much in advance... and hope to see you there!<br>
<br>
Fortune<br>
61 monk<br>
